        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer537613648" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3668306103970738084">This was the first of Ffyona&apos;s books I read and I thought it was inspirational. I could not understand why I had not come across her before. <br/><br/>It charts her tale of a walk across Africa, her relationship with her support crew and the people she meets along the way. There&apos;s no doubt she&apos;s a determined and driven woman, and it is this side of her character that dominates most of the book. However, I was especially drawn in by the rare moments where she showed her heart and softened a little. <br/><br/>Some re</span>
  <span id="freeText3668306103970738084" style="display:none">This was the first of Ffyona's books I read and I thought it was inspirational. I could not understand why I had not come across her before. <br /><br />It charts her tale of a walk across Africa, her relationship with her support crew and the people she meets along the way. There's no doubt she's a determined and driven woman, and it is this side of her character that dominates most of the book. However, I was especially drawn in by the rare moments where she showed her heart and softened a little. <br /><br />Some readers might find her a little too heartless, a little too domineering, a little too strong...but keep reading and as the book progresses you'll discover more of her character. A very worthwhile read, and one which will inspire you.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3668306103970738084" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

